and for T2/T1 ratios ranging from 0.01 to 1.0, using loga-

rithmically spaced T2 values between 10 ms and 1000

ms, but a fixed T1 of 1000 ms.

Measurements
A contemporary DESS sequence was adapted for acquisition of F1, F0, and FÀ1 within every TR, as displayed in Figure 1a. Generally, although not limited to, the same bandwidth was used for the acquisition of all echoes. To provide enough SNR in the base data for T1 and T2 calculation, some averages of the TESS scan were taken as specified below.
In vitro relaxation time mapping with TESS was performed at 1.5 T using manganese-doped spherical phantoms (0 mM, 0.05 mM, 0.125 mM, 0.25 mM, 0.5 mM MnCl2 in H2O) of about 14 cm in diameter. Longitudinal relaxation was assessed from single-slice IR turbo spin

